    "descriptionHtml": "<p><strong>Why this role is perfect for a student living in Amsterdam</strong><br>Looking for one of the best Amsterdam student jobs that blends creativity with culture? The Rijksmuseum sits at the heart of the city’s vibrant museum district and is an ideal place for students based around Roeterseiland Campus, Vondelpark, De Pijp or Science Park — and it’s just a quick bike ride from Centraal Station. If you want to build your portfolio while soaking up Amsterdam’s local vibe, this Content Intern role gives you hands-on digital experience within a leading cultural institution.</p>\n\n<p><strong>The role</strong><br>As a Content Intern you will work within the Digital Marketing &amp; Campaigns team creating creative content for the Rijksmuseum’s online channels. Daily tasks include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Developing and drafting social posts, short-form video concepts and website copy tailored to the museum’s audiences</li>\n  <li>Collaborating with designers, photographers and curators to make content assets publication-ready</li>\n  <li>Assisting with content calendars, campaign roll-out and performance monitoring</li>\n  <li>Researching trending topics and audience insights to inform creative ideas</li>\n  <li>Supporting day-to-day channel management and scheduling for online platforms</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Start date: 1 February 2026 • Duration: 6 months • Work time: 36 hours per week (full-time internship) • Location: Amsterdam</p>\n\n<p><strong>International-friendly information</strong><br>The position is part of an international workplace, however Dutch is required for this internship. This means the role is best suited for students who speak Dutch; it is not suitable for students who only speak English. If you are an international student studying in Dutch or who already uses Dutch in a professional setting, this can still be a great fit. For students searching for student jobs in Amsterdam for english speakers or jobs in Amsterdam for international students, please note that this specific vacancy requires Dutch language skills.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Practicalities</strong><br>Working hours: full-time internship (36u/week). Salary: not specified. The Rijksmuseum is centrally located and easily reached by bike or public transport — a short ride from Centraal Station and accessible from many student neighbourhoods like De Pijp and areas around Roeterseiland Campus and Science Park. The team aims to be flexible within the framework of a full-time internship; exact scheduling and any remote options will be discussed during the interview process.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Why apply?</strong><br>This is a rare opportunity to gain marketing and content experience at a world-class museum while living in Amsterdam. You’ll build a professional portfolio, work on tangible campaigns, and connect with colleagues across creative and curatorial departments — all while enjoying student life in one of Europe’s most dynamic cities.</p>\n\n<p><strong>How to apply</strong><br>Ready to apply? Use the form below to submit your application. Make sure your CV and a short cover letter (or links to relevant work) highlight your content experience, interest in culture or museums, and your Dutch language proficiency.</p>",
